rComments: course has potential but is poorly structured. it's all over the place and lectures are really sparse. you'll have to read the papers yourself to actually learn anything. tests are weird and cover topics that werent covered in class.

seems like a nice prof, but PLZ don't post your assignment guidelines 3 hours before the deadline and when most people have already submitted their stuff. plz don't post them on the discussion board...would be nice if they were posted as an anouncement so more people would have known about it.
She's nice and approachable, but her tests are very ambiguous. The questions are not designed to differentiate between good students and bad students, they just confuse everyone.
her tests are crappy... whats up with her stupid questions?
She is a good lecturer on occasions, though many of her slides contain extra information that isn't related to the main points of endocrinology. Her test was very ambiguous.
What is with her ambiguous tests? Sheesh, she needs to stop inserting extra useless information in her questions to screw people over. She seems nice enough, but at least McKay was fair in his tests.

She's really enthusiastic, super nice, super helpful. And she tries to incorporate recent findings into lectures to spark things a little. That being said, her lectures are hard to understand sometimes. It takes awhile for the materials to sink in. Her tests tend to be head scratchers.
